Risk 2: China-Taiwan tensions escalate following military drills

Categories: Geopolitical

Narrative
China's December 2025 military drills around Taiwan [1] represent ongoing pressure on the island. Despite IMF raising China's growth forecast to 4.5% for 2026 [2] and stimulus measures [3][4], geopolitical tensions could escalate. If China perceives external interference or Taiwan moves toward formal independence, military exercises could intensify into actual conflict or blockade scenarios. This would disrupt critical semiconductor supply chains, trigger US-China confrontation under 'America First' policies [5][6], and create severe market dislocations across Asia-Pacific where the portfolio has ~25% exposure. The economic stimulus might be insufficient to offset such geopolitical shocks.

Analyst Reasoning:

Plan
: Develop risk scenario where China-Taiwan tensions escalate beyond military drills to actual conflict or blockade.

Evidence Selection
: Used China's military drills [1], IMF growth forecast [2], China stimulus [3][4], and US foreign policy [5][6].

Synthesis
: Military drills show ongoing pressure; US 'America First' policy could provoke China; economic factors might not deter geopolitical actions.

Portfolio Relevance
: Portfolio has significant Asia-Pacific exposure; Taiwan conflict would disrupt global tech supply chains and trigger broader market dislocations.

Feedback & Revisions
: None

Portfolio Relevance
: Rating: High. Rationale: The portfolio's ~25% Asia-Pacific exposure makes it directly vulnerable to regional conflict. Taiwan conflict would disrupt global semiconductor supply chains affecting technology-heavy equity allocations. US-China confrontation under 'America First' policies could trigger broader trade/financial sanctions impacting global markets. Real assets with Asian exposure would face valuation pressures. The portfolio's long-horizon approach is vulnerable to regime shifts in US-China relations and Asian security architecture.

Sources

https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/12/29/china-to-stage-drills-around-taiwan-in-stern-warning-to-external-forces?utm_source=openai

https://www.scmp.com/economy/china-economy/article/3340419/imf-raises-chinas-2026-growth-forecast-45-citing-us-truce-and-stimulus-roll-out?utm_source=openai

https://www.caproasia.com/2025/07/16/china-stimulus-plan-china-issued-1-8-trillion-cny-12-9-trillion-new-cny-loans-in-2025-1st-half-to-businesses-public-institutions-households-89-55-cny-loans-issued-to-businesses-public-instit/?utm_source=openai

